channel_info.channel_name: NEETprep Course: NCERT Based NEET Preparation

video_info.title: Decided to Prepare for NEET 2026? How to PLAN your studies on Daily & Weekly basis?
video_info.description:
To Get Early Bird Discount on courses on NEETprep.com for NEET 2026 & NEET 2027, fill the Google Form from this link https://forms.gle/zup8pAsbAL6CRq4cA
1. Link of Jumbo Test Series: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/5897-Jumbo-Test-Series--NEET-#study-material
2. Link of Target Batch for NEET 2026: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/3785-NEET---Target-Batch 
3. Link of Target Batch for NEET 2027: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/5666
4.  Masterclass in Biology BOOK (to Target 360/360 in NERT Bio): https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/4313 Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

#neet #neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet2027

video_info.title: Before CHALLENGE WINDOW Closes - CONFUSION on 5 Bio Questions in NEET 2025 Explained by Dr. Sharma
video_info.description:
If you feel strongly about challenging these questions,  please fill Google Form from the link https://forms.gle/Uanmo79D2ouXE4Hw9 and we will share TEXT of the explanation provided by Dr. Sharma in this video
Link of Dr. Sharma's Telegram Channel: https://t.me/mibdrnksharma
1. Link of Masterclass in Biology (Book/Online Bio Q Bank) from Dr. N.K.Sharma: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/5832
2. Link of Bio Prodigy (‚ÄúBio Only‚Äù Test Series): https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/2960

Fill Google Form from the link https://forms.gle/zup8pAsbAL6CRq4cA to get On Phone Discount on our MCQ Practice & Testing courses.

How to Use Target Batch? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SQZYU-FMjJk&t=124s
11th Wasted? How to Organise studies for NEET 2026? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WWuECrl4jMI&t=19s

In this video, Kapil Sir and Dr. NK Sharma explain the process of challenging certain questions in the NEET 2025 exam within the NEET challenge window. They specifically highlight the confusion surrounding questions like whether figs are vegetarian or non-vegetarian due to the presence of wasps in the fruit. This is a prime example of how small wording changes can create significant confusion for students.

Dr. Sharma emphasizes the importance of critical analysis when it comes to NEET exam questions. He encourages students to review the NEET 2025 answer key carefully and challenge any questions that may seem ambiguous. This is particularly relevant for biology questions, where interpretations like the vegetarian status of figs have sparked ongoing debates in both academic and public spheres.

The video urges NEET aspirants to take full advantage of the NEET answer key challenge window. By doing so, they can ensure accuracy and avoid misunderstandings in their studies. As Kapil Sir advises, practicing NEET level MCQs and preparing with resources like NCERT-based questions can help students tackle tricky questions and improve their overall NEET preparation for 2026 and beyond..

#neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet #kapilsir 
 Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

comments.author: @sigmarule...2065
comments.raw_text:
In assertion-reason questions, a true reason must fully and directly explain the assertion, not just be ‚Äòrelated‚Äô.

Assertion (A) is True:

The Golgi apparatus indeed packages and distributes materials (proteins/lipids) from the ER to intracellular/extracellular targets.

Reason (R) is True:

Vesicles from the ER fuse with the¬†cis¬†face, are modified, and exit via the¬†trans¬†face.

Why (R) Does NOT Explain (A)?

My submission:

(R) describes the process, not the¬†primary function.

(R) explains¬†how¬†materials move through the Golgi (structural mechanism), but it does not address¬†why¬†the Golgi performs this role (functional purpose).

What is missing for Option to be the correct answer?

(A) emphasizes the¬†functional outcome¬†(delivery to targets), while (R) only describes the¬†transport route¬†(cis-to-trans flow).

For (R) to fully explain (A), it must connect vesicle trafficking to¬†sorting, tagging, or destination-specific delivery [Golgi is a sort of post office].

For example, "The Golgi modifies and tags proteins with signals to direct them to specific targets.‚Äù

Since the ‚Äòwhy‚Äô is not explained directly by R, the correct answer should be option 4.
comments.cleaned_text: In assertion-reason questions, a true reason must fully and directly explain the assertion, not just be ‚Äòrelated‚Äô. Reason (R) is True: Vesicles from the ER fuse with the cis face, are modified, and exit via the trans face. Why (R) Does NOT Explain (A)? My submission: (R) describes the process, not the primary function. (R) explains how materials move through the Golgi (structural mechanism), but it does not address why the Golgi performs this role (functional purpose). What is missing for Option to be the correct answer? (A) emphasizes the functional outcome (delivery to targets), while (R) only describes the transport route (cis-to-trans flow). For (R) to fully explain (A), it must connect vesicle trafficking to sorting, tagging, or destination-specific delivery [Golgi is a sort of post office]. For example, "The Golgi modifies and tags proteins with signals to direct them to specific targets.‚Äù Since the ‚Äòwhy‚Äô is not explained directly by R, the correct answer should be option 4.

comments.raw_text:
those who think that in golgi ques , R is not explaining A, can write this (i am also challenging this ques)..
Both Assertion and Reason are right ,but I think reason is not explaining  assertion.
Because *statement-2* is only telling us -how materials move through Golgi body (it is talking about its structural aspect).

But to prove that   statement-2   explains  statement -1  we need to know- why it's primary function is to package materials (and that cannot be explained by talking about its structure).

I think this question can also be considered like this:-

Assertion: A car‚Äôs primary function is to transport people.
Reason: The car has an engine in front and an exhaust at the back.

here reason doesn‚Äôt explain assertion.

comments.author: @Royalempire-e2o
comments.raw_text:
Step 1: Understand the problem
The problem is asking to find the magnification of a microscope given the focal length of the objective lens, the focal length of the eyepiece, and the tube length.

Step 2: Identify the given values
The focal length of the objective lens (f_o) = 2 cm
The focal length of the eyepiece (f_e) = 4 cm (though typically, the eyepiece has a larger focal length than the objective, we'll proceed with the given values)
The tube length (L) = 25 cm (this is not directly used in the standard magnification formula but is relevant for the total magnification calculation)
The distance of distinct vision (D) = 40 cm (a standard value for the near point)

Step 3: Recall the formula for magnification of a microscope
The total magnification (M) of a microscope is given by the formula: M = M_o * M_e, where M_o is the magnification of the objective lens and M_e is the magnification of the eyepiece.

Step 4: Calculate the magnification of the objective lens (M_o) and the eyepiece (M_e)
M_o = L / f_o (for the objective lens, considering the tube length as the image distance for the objective)
M_e = (1 + D/f_e) (for the eyepiece, using the near point)

Step 5: Apply the given values to the formula
First, let's correct the understanding: The actual formula for total magnification is M = (L/f_o) * (1 + D/f_e).

M = (25/2) * (1 + 40/4)

Step 6: Perform the calculation
M = (12.5) * (1 + 10)
M = 12.5 * 11
M = 137.5

Step 7: Round the answer to the nearest option
The closest answer to 137.5 is 125 (option 2) or 150 (option 3), given the available choices.

Step 8: Choose the closest answer
The closest value to 137.5 among the given options is 150 (though not exact, it's the nearest).

The best answer is (3) 150.

video_info.title: If you KNOW, You will NOT CRACK NEET 2025, What should you do?
video_info.description:
Subscribe this channel for Practical NEET Guidance!!! Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

#neet #neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet2027

Insights from Rachit...who was very disappointed after the exam BUT is now going to be getting a top rank!!! So Chill Guys...Rank Matters and score does not!!!

The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. video_info.title: 8 Month Time Table for NEET 2026 dropper | Complete Syllabus by 31st Jan  #neetdroppers #neetprep
video_info.description:
How to Use Target Batch? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SQZYU-FMjJk&t=124s
11th Wasted? How to Organise studies for NEET 2026? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WWuECrl4jMI&t=19s
Fill Google Form from the link https://forms.gle/zup8pAsbAL6CRq4cA to get On Phone Discount on our MCQ Practice & Testing courses.
Test Planner for NEET 2026 Classroom Test Series has been UPLOADED on the link https://t.me/NEETprep/

In this video, Kapil Sir explains the ideal time table for NEET 2026 aspirants, especially those planning to take a drop for better preparation. He outlines a clear strategy based on the number of study hours available, emphasizing the importance of balancing NEET syllabus coverage with focused NEET physics lectures and NEET chemistry lectures. Kapil Sir highlights that along with thorough theory study, practicing MCQs and giving regular tests are crucial for effective NEET exam preparation. Whether you‚Äôre looking for the best NEET preparation course or an online strategy, this guidance is essential for cracking NEET 2026, particularly for droppers following Kapil Sir‚Äôs proven dropper strategy and timetable.

#neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet #kapilsir Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

#neet #neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet2027

Link of Target Batch (Final Push): https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/5072-Target-Batch--Final-Push
To Get Early Bird Discount on courses on NEETprep.com, fill the Google Form from this link https://forms.gle/zup8pAsbAL6CRq4cA

How to USE Target Batch? https://youtu.be/wlFJb4UXOaA

How to USE Target Batch for SIGNIFICANT Improvement in your Performance? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qzfvSq8L3Kg


Following are 6 best courses for MCQ Practice & Testing on NEETprep.com
MCQ practice:
1. Link of Target Batch for NEET 2025: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/3521-NEET---Target-Batch
2. Link of Target Batch for NEET 2026: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/3785-NEET---Target-Batch 
3.  Masterclass in Biology BOOK (to Target 360/360 in NERT Bio): https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/4313
Testing:
1. Classroom Tests in 200 Centers: https://forms.gle/a7rSu9vtUrZNqjxJ7
2. Jumbo Test Series: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/3160
3. Bio Only Test Series:  https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/2960 Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

video_info.title: Part 2 of 3 - Documents to be UPLOADED (X Marksheet & Category Certificate) for NEET 2025
video_info.description:
In next video, we will cover every detail you need to understand about the following:
(i) Present Address (ii)Permanent Address (iii)Identity Proof

In 3 videos between Rakesh sir & Kapil sir, we have covered all the aspects of documents for the following:
1. Images to be uploaded
2. Category Certificate
3. Class X  Marksheet &  Certificate
4. Present Address
5. Permanent Address
6. Identity Proof Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

#neet #neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet2027

video_info.title: LAUNCHING  ASCEND - (Gradual Pace) Classroom Test Series for NEET 2026 DROPPERS!!!
video_info.description:
To get EARLY BIRD Discount, on Classroom Test Series & Course Bundles, fill Google Form from the link https://forms.gle/zup8pAsbAL6CRq4cA
Test Planner for NEET 2026 Classroom Test Series has been UPLOADED on the link https://t.me/NEETprep/
As explained by Kapil sir in the video, in addition to tests given in Test Planner, additionally, you will get 2 BONUS Tests in this test series on 8th June (Online) & 15th June (Classroom) to get you started early...you should attempt even if your syllabus is not complete!!!
Bio: The Living World, Biological Classification, Plant Kingdom, Animal Kingdom, Structural Organisation in Animals
Chem: Some Basic Concepts Of Chemistry, Structure of Atom, Classification of Elements & Periodicity, Chemical Bonding
Phy: Units & Measurements, Motion in a Straight Line, Motion in a Plane, Laws of Motion, Work, Energy & Power Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

#neet #neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet2027

video_info.title: Part 3 of 3 - Documents to be UPLOADED (Identity Proof, Present & Permanent Address) for NEET 2025
video_info.description:
Final video from the series of 3 videos covering exact details of remaining documents!!!  In 3 videos between Rakesh sir & Kapil sir, we have covered all the aspects of documents for the following:
1. Images to be uploaded
2. Category Certificate
3. Class X  Marksheet &  Certificate
4. Present Address
5. Permanent Address
6. Identity Proof Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

#neet #neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet2027

video_info.title: HOW to use Target Batch for NEET 2026 (No Lectures, Only MCQ Practice & Testing)?
video_info.description:
To get SUPER Discount on MCQ Practice & Testing Courses for NEET 2026 & NEET 2027, fill Google Form from the link https://forms.gle/zup8pAsbAL6CRq4cA

JOIN Exclusive Courses for DEDICATED MCQ Practice & Testing (No Lectures or Live Classes) for NEET 2026 & NEET 2027 from the links below:
 1. Target Batch (NEET 2026) - https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/3785
 2. Target Batch (NEET 2027) - https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/5666
 3. Jumbo Test Series (NEET 2026) - https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/5897 


In this video, Kapil Sir explains how to use the Target Batch NEETprep for effective NEET 2025 and NEET 2026 preparation. Regular question practice with the NEETprep Target Batch can significantly improve your score in the NEET exam. With this NEET preparation online course, you get smart features like bookmarking questions, recommended MCQs for NEET, and recommended PYQs for NEET at different difficulty levels. Kapil Sir demonstrates how the Target Batch 2026 helps NEET aspirants clear doubts, perform quick revisions, take tests, generate DPPs, and much more.

Since NCERT Books are the most important resource for NEET syllabus preparation, all the NCERT back exercises are converted into MCQs for better practice. Kapil Sir, the founder of NEETprep, has been guiding students for years with the right tips and support for NEET exam preparation. The NEET exam is challenging, and if you want to crack NEET 2025 or NEET 2026, you need to practice regularly and give timely tests using the NEETprep test series.

Over the years, more than 7000 students have secured seats in top government medical colleges like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, and UCMS by following this best NEET preparation course. Whether you're searching for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want daily NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep‚Äôs Target Batch is the perfect choice to boost your success in NEET preparation.

#neet #neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet2027

video_info.title: What HAAPENED on 4th May (NEET 2025 Exam Day)? The Super Event Explained!!!
video_info.description:
Students, we want to make a Separate Group for NEET 2025 aspirants (so that you can interact with other NEET 2025 aspirants and plan your next steps). You can join by filling Google Form from the link https://forms.gle/Uanmo79D2ouXE4Hw9 THIS IS STRICTLY INVITE ONLY GROUP.

You should be on this group only if you are scoring above 400...because you have a chance. Why we are saying 400? One big coaching is predicting Cutoff at 505 & another big coaching is predicting cutoff at 430!!!

Share this video NOW. Help understand parents & students about the low score you are getting (or your child is getting). The paper was SUPER TOUGH.
Caution: The data might have SAMPLE Bias and it is best to wait for FINAL RESULT from NTA in June!!! video_info.title: 11th Wasted? #restart to CRACK NEET 2026 Starts RIGHT NOW!!! Step by Step Plan INSIDE.
video_info.description:
Google Sheet Link with Sample Priority Plan: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1wJjX5GxEv9KV8A-r723EEHOxGsYrrhXihJTr2ENOavw/edit?gid=0#gid=0

1. Link of Target Batch for NEET 2026: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/3785-NEET---Target-Batch 
2.  Masterclass in Biology BOOK (to Target 360/360 in NERT Bio): https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/4313

Link of Jeetu Bhaiya video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DC-UF0iKiSY Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

#neet #neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet2027

To Get Early Bird Discount on courses on NEETprep.com, fill the Google Form from this link https://forms.gle/zup8pAsbAL6CRq4cA

How to USE Target Batch for SIGNIFICANT Improvement in your Performance? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qzfvSq8L3Kg


Following are 6 best courses for MCQ Practice & Testing on NEETprep.com
MCQ practice:
1. Link of Target Batch for NEET 2025: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/3521-NEET---Target-Batch
2. Link of Target Batch for NEET 2026: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/3785-NEET---Target-Batch 
3.  Masterclass in Biology BOOK (to Target 360/360 in NERT Bio): https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/4313
Testing:
1. Classroom Tests in 200 Centers: https://forms.gle/a7rSu9vtUrZNqjxJ7
2. Jumbo Test Series: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/3160
3. Bio Only Test Series:  https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/2960 Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

video_info.description:
Want to Enrol in NEETbeforeNEET ClassroomTest on 20th April   Fill Google Form from the link https://forms.gle/a7rSu9vtUrZNqjxJ7
PDF of Final Test last year: https://t.me/NEETprep/29176
PDF of Main Day & Reserve Day on 20th April: https://t.me/NEETprep/29177

Time Table PDF UPLOADED on the link https://t.me/NEETprep/28928
Fill Google Form from the link  https://forms.gle/Tp3jfDAjgxygpzoZ9 to get Access of Super Revision Google Drive.

How to attempt Tests in Pen Paper OMR format? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oezTpj0HG6A
Link of Target Batch (Final Push): https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/5072-Target-Batch--Final-Push
To Get Early Bird Discount on courses on NEETprep.com, fill the Google Form from this link https://forms.gle/zup8pAsbAL6CRq4cA

How to USE Target Batch? https://youtu.be/wlFJb4UXOaA

Final Push explanation video: https://youtu.be/H3LB-x4RJjo?si=h38Ht2CvFyRQLfZU

How to USE Target Batch for SIGNIFICANT Improvement in your Performance? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qzfvSq8L3Kg


Following are 6 best courses for MCQ Practice & Testing on NEETprep.com
MCQ practice:
1. Link of Target Batch for NEET 2025: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/3521-NEET---Target-Batch
2. Link of Target Batch for NEET 2026: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/3785-NEET---Target-Batch 
3.  Masterclass in Biology BOOK (to Target 360/360 in NERT Bio): https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/4313
Testing:
1. Classroom Tests in 200 Centers: https://forms.gle/a7rSu9vtUrZNqjxJ7
2. Jumbo Test Series: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/3160
3. Bio Only Test Series:  https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/2960 Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

Testing:
1. Classroom Tests in 200 Centers: https://forms.gle/a7rSu9vtUrZNqjxJ7

He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

video_info.title: Unit #1 (NEET Bio) New NCERT DISCREPANCIES Confirmed by Dr. N.K.Sharma!!!
video_info.description:
Dr. Sharma will POST questions on NCERT discrepancies on his Telegram channel https://t.me/mibdrnksharma
Share your FEEDBACK on the video. Also, Share other NCERT discrepancies you know in COMMENTS Section of the video so that Dr. Sharma can address them in next videos.

Want to Practice MCQs & Mock Tests DESIGNED by Dr. Sharma himself (like questions that are posted on this channel)? JOIN NOW from the links:
1. Masterclass in Biology (Online Q Bank) from the link https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/4379
2. "Bio Only" Test Series to target 360/360 in NEET Bio: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/2960
3. Revision Package (Masterclass in Biology) containing 2000 Most Valuable Questions: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/5336
4. Bio Prodigy "Bio Only" Home Test Series: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/3719 Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

#neet #neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet2027

video_info.title: Should I take a drop for NEET 2026? | How to DECIDE?
video_info.description:
Link of NEETprep Telegram Channel: https://t.me/neetprep

Fill Google Form from the link https://forms.gle/zup8pAsbAL6CRq4cA to get On Phone Discount on our MCQ Practice & Testing courses.

How to Use Target Batch? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SQZYU-FMjJk&t=124s
11th Wasted? How to Organise studies for NEET 2026? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WWuECrl4jMI&t=19s

Should I take a drop for NEET 2026 or not? This is the most important question that many students are asking just after the NEET 2025 exam. Deciding whether to take a drop for NEET 2026 can be tough, but it‚Äôs a decision you have to make with careful thought and personal commitment.

Kapil Sir emphasizes that motivation and dedication play a huge role in this decision. He urges NEET aspirants to think deeply about their dreams of becoming a doctor and reflect on their personal goals. With the possibility of a drop in NEET 2026 cutoff, which might be around 550 marks (down from 653 last year), aspirants need to decide if they are ready for this challenge.

For those considering a drop for NEET 2026, Kapil Sir shares a crucial piece of advice: If you are committed to studying 10-12 hours a day, no matter what‚Äîwhether it's a Sunday, festival, or family function‚Äîyou should consider taking the drop. If you aren't fully committed, it's better to move on and focus on other opportunities.

NEET preparation, especially for NEET 2026, requires dedication, and Kapil Sir‚Äôs dropper strategy will guide you through this rigorous journey. So, ask yourself: Are you ready to take that step for NEET 2026?

#neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet #kapilsir 

 Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

#neet #neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet2027

comments.raw_text:
If you are just starting with any concept, begin by attempting the absorb MCQs to clear the basics. Then, move on to the recommended MCQs, starting with easy questions, followed by medium ones, and finally, practice some difficult questions as well.

Once you've completed the topic or chapter, generate a DPP (Daily Practice Problem) and solve it to assess how well you've understood the material.

Note: If you are unable to solve any question, first check the provided hint, followed by the video or audio solution. Additionally, bookmark all the questions that you couldn't solve.

video_info.description:
1. Link of Masterclass in Biology (Book/Online Bio Q Bank) from Dr. N.K.Sharma: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/5832
2. Link of Bio Prodigy (‚ÄúBio Only‚Äù Test Series): https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/2960

Fill Google Form from the link https://forms.gle/zup8pAsbAL6CRq4cA to get On Phone Discount on our MCQ Practice & Testing courses.

How to Use Target Batch? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SQZYU-FMjJk&t=124s
11th Wasted? How to Organise studies for NEET 2026? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WWuECrl4jMI&t=19s

In this video, Kapil Sir explains that many NEET aspirants like you have decided to take a drop this year to prepare for NEET 2026. One common challenge you might be facing is that your coaching is going slow, even though you‚Äôre ready to move faster. You‚Äôve already studied most chapters during your previous attempts, and you probably don‚Äôt want to repeat the same content unnecessarily.

To help you with this, Kapil Sir shares the NEET 2026 Dropper Complete Study Plan, perfect for those wondering how to study fast for NEET. He suggests that while your coaching might be covering every chapter in detail, if you only need a quick revision, you can skip the lectures and directly move on to question practice ‚Äî which is more important and exam-focused.

This method is trusted by many toppers and is considered the best source for NEET preparation. If you‚Äôre searching for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want to know how to crack NEET, this video and study plan will help you stay ahead ‚Äî whether you're preparing for NEET 2026 or even planning for NEET 2027.

#neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet #kapilsir 
 Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

#neet #neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet2027

video_info.title: Why Classroom Testing is VERY VERY Important to CRACK NEET?
video_info.description:
Test Planners for Classroom Test Series UPLOADED on the link https://t.me/neetprep

Fill Google Form from the link https://forms.gle/zup8pAsbAL6CRq4cA to get On Phone Discount on our MCQ Practice & Testing courses.

How to Use Target Batch? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SQZYU-FMjJk&t=124s
11th Wasted? How to Organise studies for NEET 2026? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WWuECrl4jMI&t=19s

Most NEET aspirants make a big mistake, and this mistake becomes a reason why they are unable to crack the NEET exam. This mistake is not giving tests, and if tests are given in good numbers, students often cheat in the test, especially if the test is online or in the coaching centers they are preparing for NEET. The solution for this problem is to join an offline test series, which provides a complete picture of your preparation, as you will not know anyone at the center, and the test is conducted in NEET exam-like conditions. This way, you will get the real picture of your preparation.

Classroom testing provides a structured environment that simulates the actual NEET exam, helping students prepare effectively. Regular testing in a classroom setting allows students to analyze their performance and improve their exam strategies. The importance of classroom tests is emphasized due to the high stakes of the NEET exam, where students have only one chance each year.

The video highlights the widespread availability of classroom test centers across India, making it accessible for students in various districts. The speaker shares success stories of students who performed well in NEET after participating in the classroom test series, reinforcing its effectiveness.

#neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet #kapilsir 

 Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

#neet #neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet2027

In this video, Kapil Sir has explained, how to use PYQs during your NEET preparation. Most NEET aspirants either do not attempt PYQs or use them in the wrong way. PYQs are the best method to predict the pattern of the exam and form the pattern I mean the weightage of the  chapters from Physics chemistry and biology. Kapil Sir explained the best use of PYQs, by applying this method you can actually increase your scores in the NEET 2025 exam. 
Sit back, grab a pen and a paper, and start understanding the method properly

00:00 Coming Up

If you want to talk to Kapil sir to understand how you can CRACK NEET by studying from the NEETprep Online Video course, you can call him at 9667591930

#neetpyq #neet #neetpreparation #neetprep Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. Kapil Sir recommends joining Dr. Anand Mani's Residential Program for NEET aspirants because it offers a structured and immersive learning environment tailored for success in the NEET examination. The program is designed to provide comprehensive support, ensuring students are well-prepared both academically and mentally.

Key Features of the Residential Program:

* Expert-Led Coaching: Students receive instruction from Dr. Anand Mani and a team of experienced NEET faculty, ensuring high-quality education. 
* Comprehensive Curriculum: The program covers the entire Class 11 and 12 NCERT syllabus in depth, focusing on Physics, Chemistry, and Biology. 
* Residential Campus: A disciplined and focused learning environment with hostel facilities allows students to concentrate fully on their studies without external distractions. 
* Regular Assessments: Weekly tests, full-length mock exams, and NEET-level practice papers help track progress and identify areas for improvement. 
* Personalized Mentorship: One-on-one doubt sessions and personalized mentoring boost student confidence and address individual learning needs. 
* Exclusive Study Material: Students have access to NEET-focused modules, notes, question banks, and previous year papers for thorough preparation. 
* State-of-the-Art Infrastructure: Well-equipped classrooms, library access, and online learning support enhance the overall learning experience.

Who Should Join?

* Students entering Class 11 who aim for NEET 2027 success.
* Aspirants seeking early preparation with structured guidance and a strong foundation.
* Those desiring personalized mentorship, continuous evaluation, and an immersive learning experience.

video_info.description:
PDF of Tough Paper which Rachit gave uploaded on the link https://t.me/NEETprep/29850
Fill Google Form from the link https://forms.gle/zup8pAsbAL6CRq4cA to get On Phone Discount on our MCQ Practice & Testing courses.
PDF
Test Planner for NEET 2026 Classroom Test Series has been UPLOADED on the link https://t.me/NEETprep/
How to Use Target Batch? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SQZYU-FMjJk&t=124s
11th Wasted? How to Organise studies for NEET 2026? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WWuECrl4jMI&t=19s

In this video, Kapil Sir explains the ideal time table for NEET 2026 aspirants, especially those planning to take a drop for better preparation. He outlines a clear strategy based on the number of study hours available, emphasizing the importance of balancing NEET syllabus coverage with focused NEET physics lectures and NEET chemistry lectures. Kapil Sir highlights that along with thorough theory study, practicing MCQs and giving regular tests are crucial for effective NEET exam preparation. Whether you‚Äôre looking for the best NEET preparation course or an online strategy, this guidance is essential for cracking NEET 2026, particularly for droppers following Kapil Sir‚Äôs proven dropper strategy and timetable.

#neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet #kapilsir Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

#neet #neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet2027

video_info.title: Everything EXPLAINED about Admit Card for NEET 2025 - Must Watch (MIGHT BE FUNNY) till the end!!!
video_info.description:
Posted on NEETprep Telegram Channel (https://t.me/neetprep): PDFs of Top 20 PYQs for all 82 chapters.

Till NEET 2025, we will post Top 5 PYQs from each of the 82 chapters!!! Happy Studies & Best of Luck.

To get EARLY BIRD Discount, on Classroom Test Series & Course Bundles, fill Google Form from the link https://forms.gle/zup8pAsbAL6CRq4cA
Test Planner for NEET 2026 Classroom Test Series has been UPLOADED on the link https://t.me/NEETprep/29456 Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

#neet #neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet2027

video_info.description:
Best source to prepare for NEET 2026
To Get Early Bird Discount on courses on NEETprep.com for NEET 2026 & NEET 2027, fill the Google Form from this link https://forms.gle/zup8pAsbAL6CRq4cA
1. Link of Jumbo Test Series: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/5897-Jumbo-Test-Series--NEET-#study-material
2. Link of Target Batch for NEET 2026: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/3785-NEET---Target-Batch 
3. Link of Target Batch for NEET 2027: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/5666
4.  Masterclass in Biology BOOK (to Target 360/360 in NERT Bio): https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/4313

In this video, Kapil Sir has explained how you can crack the NEET 2026 exam. As the time remaining for the exam is not more than a year from now, you have to be more cautious. Lot of students ask that the test series in their NEET coaching is not that good, so can a student join more than 1 test series for NEET? 
Well, yes, you can join 2 test series, and to solve this problem, NEETprep has launched the Jumbo Test series where you can test yourself and compete on an all-India level.

#neet2026 #neet2027 #neet #neetpreparation #neetexam Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

#neet #neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet2027

video_info.description:

Want Details of Classroom Test Series in 250+ Centers across India? Please fill Google Form from the link https://forms.gle/a7rSu9vtUrZNqjxJ7

To Get Early Bird Discount on courses on NEETprep.com, fill the Google Form from this link https://forms.gle/zup8pAsbAL6CRq4cA

How to USE Target Batch? https://youtu.be/wlFJb4UXOaA

Final Push explaination video: https://youtu.be/H3LB-x4RJjo?si=h38Ht2CvFyRQLfZU

How to USE Target Batch for SIGNIFICANT Improvement in your Performance? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qzfvSq8L3Kg


Following are 6 best courses for MCQ Practice & Testing on NEETprep.com
MCQ practice:
1. Link of Target Batch for NEET 2025: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/3521-NEET---Target-Batch
2. Link of Target Batch for NEET 2026: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/3785-NEET---Target-Batch 
3.  Masterclass in Biology BOOK (to Target 360/360 in NERT Bio): https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/4313
Testing:
1. Classroom Tests in 200 Centers: https://forms.gle/a7rSu9vtUrZNqjxJ7
2. Jumbo Test Series: https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/3160
3. Bio Only Test Series:  https://www.neetprep.com/neet-course/2960 Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

#neet #neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet2027

video_info.description:
Fill Google Form from the link https://forms.gle/zup8pAsbAL6CRq4cA to get On Phone Discount on our MCQ Practice & Testing courses.
PDF
Test Planner for NEET 2026 & NEET 2027 Classroom Test Series has been UPLOADED on the link https://t.me/NEETprep/
How to Use Target Batch? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SQZYU-FMjJk&t=124s
11th Wasted? How to Organise studies for NEET 2026? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WWuECrl4jMI&t=19s



#neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet #kapilsir 
 Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

#neet #neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet2027

1. Absorb before you solve (just go through the video explanations of these questions to know how to attempt MCQs)
2. Recommended MCQs
3. NCERT Back Exercise (converted to MCQs)
4. NCERT Solution (converted to MCQs)
5. NCERT Exemplar

video_info.title: Physics in NEET 2026 will be JEE Advanced Level? | How to prepare for NEET physics?
video_info.description:
PDFs of Analysis of NEET 2025, NEET 2024 & NEET 2021 Physics UPLOADED on NEETprep Telegram Channel (https://t.me/neetprep)
Fill Google Form from the link https://forms.gle/zup8pAsbAL6CRq4cA to get On Phone Discount on our MCQ Practice & Testing courses.
PDF
Test Planner for NEET 2026 & NEET 2027 Classroom Test Series has been UPLOADED on the link https://t.me/NEETprep/
How to Use Target Batch? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SQZYU-FMjJk&t=124s
11th Wasted? How to Organise studies for NEET 2026? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WWuECrl4jMI&t=19s

In this video, Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, along with Ankur Sir, addresses the common doubts of NEET aspirants who are uncertain about the level of NEET 2026 Physics. Many students are panicking and wondering, ‚ÄúDo I need to prepare for JEE Advanced level for NEET Physics?‚Äù

Ankur Sir clarifies this confusion by analyzing the NEET 2025 Physics paper. He explains that while the paper was lengthy and had a few challenging questions, none of the questions were of JEE Advanced level. A few questions matched the JEE Mains level in terms of concept and application, but not a single one required the depth of JEE Advanced preparation.

This means that if you start preparing Physics for NEET 2026 at the JEE Advanced level, you might end up exhausting yourself and lose focus on what really matters‚Äîaccuracy and speed within a limited time. NEET Physics is not just about toughness; it's about handling moderately challenging questions smartly within a strict time limit.

So, if you're asking, ‚ÄúHow to prepare Physics for NEET?‚Äù‚Äîthe answer is clear: level up your preparation strategically, but do not overprepare to the point where you lose grip on NEET-specific fundamentals and efficient problem-solving.


#neet2026 #neetprep #neetpreparation #neet #kapilsir

https://top.neetprep.com : Link of NEETprep Talent Scholarship (NTS) Exam on 8th, 9th & 10th April for NEET 2027 asprirants....DETAILS COMING SOON!!! Kapil Sir, founder of NEETprep, is helping students crack NEET with the right guidance and regular support. He has been guiding students for NEET preparation for many years. The NEET exam was tough this year, and if you want to crack NEET, you have to practice more questions and give regular tests to get maximum marks in your NEET 2026 or NEET 2027 exam. NEETprep and Kapil Sir can help you practice NEET level MCQs that are based on NCERT, which is the best source for NEET preparation. In the last few years, more than 7000 students have been selected in top institutes like AIIMS Delhi, MAMC, VMMC, UCMS, and other government medical colleges. If you're looking for the best source to prepare for NEET, or want regular NEET MCQ practice, NEETprep is the right place for you.

video_info.title: Understanding d and f Block Elements for NEET 2025 | Chemistry for NEET with Shashi Sir
video_info.description:
In this video, Shashi Sir dives deep into the world of d and f block elements, offering crucial insights for NEET 2025 aspirants. Starting with an introduction to the electronic configurations of these elements, he links their properties to earlier lessons on chemical bonding and the periodic table.

Throughout the session, Shashi Sir focuses on the unique behaviors of elements like niobium and technetium, showcasing their relevance in NEET Chemistry. video_info.title: Understanding KSP: Solubility Product Made Easy for NEET 2025 Aspirants | Shashi Sir #neet2025
video_info.description:
In this video, Shashi Sir demystifies the concept of KSP (Solubility Product Constant) for NEET 2025 aspirants. He breaks down common misconceptions and explains why KSP is not as difficult as it seems. Topics covered include:

The definition of KSP and how to calculate it for various salts.

The relationship between KSP and ionic products.

The impact of common ions on KSP.

How pH levels relate to the solubility product.

Advanced concepts like the connection between KSP, Gibbs free energy (ŒîG), and enthalpy (ŒîH).

How factors like temperature and solute nature affect solubility.

This video is perfect for NEET aspirants aiming to master this important concept and ace their exams. Don't miss out on these insights to boost your understanding of KSP!

In this video, Shashi Sir dives deep into the world of d and f block elements, offering crucial insights for NEET 2025 aspirants. Starting with an introduction to the electronic configurations of these elements, he links their properties to earlier lessons on chemical bonding and the periodic table.

Throughout the session, Shashi Sir focuses on the unique behaviors of elements like niobium and technetium, showcasing their relevance in NEET Chemistry. Shashi Sir compares the solubility of fluorine with KF, showing how the KSP values differ significantly, and how this impacts solubility calculations. video_info.title: Important Terms of Biomolecules with Examples | #neet2025 #biomolecules
video_info.description:
In this video, Shashi Sir explains the fundamental concepts related to disaccharides, crucial for NEET Chemistry. He dives into key terms such as "pyranose" and "glycosidic linkage," helping you understand their significance in biochemistry.

Shashi Sir begins with the structure of pyranose, a six-membered ring that includes an oxygen atom, and its role in disaccharides. He then moves on to glycosidic linkages, explaining these covalent bonds formed via a condensation reaction, specifically focusing on the anomeric carbon.

You'll also learn about the various types of glycosidic linkages, including 1-2, 1-4, and 1-6 linkages, and how they relate to the anomeric carbon. The video introduces alpha and beta configurations, breaking down the differences between their trans and cis forms, especially in relation to functional groups.

This video is a must-watch for NEET aspirants looking to strengthen their understanding of carbohydrate chemistry.
